President Cyril Ramaphosa will address the nation at 8.30pm on Wednesday. The president is expected to speak about South Africa’s ongoing measures to manage the spread of COVID-19 through the implementation of a risk-adjusted strategy. * Editor's note: The live event is scheduled to start at 8.30pm. JOHANNESBURG - President Cyril Ramaphosa will address the nation at 8.30pm on Wednesday. The president is expected to speak about South Africa’s ongoing measures to manage the spread of COVID-19 through the implementation of a risk-adjusted strategy. READ: COVID-19: The worst is yet to come says Ramaphosa The president’s address follows a number of meetings of Cabinet and the National Coronavirus Command Council. Ramaphosa's spokesperson Khusela Diko earlier said Health Minister Zweli Mkhize would give an update on the progress made in screening, tracing and testing of COVID-19.